<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, Zhu &amp; Song, 2005" authorityName="Zhang, Zhu &amp; Song" authorityYear="2005" box="[683,1138,152,178]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pennatus">
<emphasis box="[683,818,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">P. pennatus</emphasis>
Zhang, Zhu &amp; Song, 2005
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the shapes of bulbal appendix and procursus, and the chitinized triangular plate of the epigynum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
